definition.value: A very long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that is the S-icosanoyl derivative of coenzyme A.
A glycosylalditol consisting of a beta-D-galactofuranosyl residue and a D-mannitol residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
The S-itaconyl derivative of coenzyme A.
A beta-D-Glcp-(1->3)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of lactic acid.
An octadecadienoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of linoleic acid.
